messages.message:
@Bastiane can you confirm the answer to this question?
> 1. did you navigate away or go to another tab while re-classification is occurring? the blue dot goes away after ~10s
@Siya keeping the indicators until the user has scrolled past the doc is definitely feasible, but i think that this isn’t the best idea for 2 reasons

1. in Bastiane’s screenshot, she only has 3 docs, so i don’t think this idea will impact discoverability in Bastiane’s example
2. it’ll be difficult to debug the lack of indicators if a user reports that they didn’t see any indicator
if we really want to increase discoverability, i think we can show the indicator until the user selects the document or the user reloads the page
